Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Bring a #large saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil for the potatoes.

Chop the @baking potato{1} into 2cm chunks (peel first if you prefer).

Trim the @parsnip{3}, then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into 2cm chunks.

Peel the @garlic cloves{2} but keep the cloves whole.

When boiling, add the potatoes, parsnips and whole garlic cloves to the water and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim the @carrot{3}, then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

Pop the carrots onto one side of a #large baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{2%tbsp}, sprinkle over the @dried rosemary{1%sachet} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

Pop the @British Cumberland sausages{4} onto the other side of the #baking tray{}.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

When the oven's hot, bake the sausages and carrots on the top shelf until the sausages are golden brown and cooked through and the carrots are tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The sausages are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Turn the sausages and carrots halfway through.

Meanwhile, pour the @water for the jus{200%ml} into another #small saucepan{}. Bring to the boil on high heat.

Stir in the @red wine jus paste{22%grams}, then reduce the heat to medium-low. Allow the sauce to bubble and thicken, stirring regularly, ~{7-8%minutes}.

> TIP: If your red wine jus paste has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Once thickened, remove from the heat and cover to keep warm. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

Once the potatoes and parsnips are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat.

Add a knob of @butter{knob} and a splash of @milk{splash}(if you have any) and mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm.

When everything's ready, transfer the sausages and carrots to your plates.

Share out the mash alongside (reheat first if needed) and spoon over the red wine jus to finish (reheat the jus first if needed).

Enjoy!